```regex
\d{3}-[a-zA-Z0-9]{3}\.usfm
```

This regex pattern will match filenames in the desired format, where:

- `\d{3}` matches three digits,
- `-` is a literal hyphen,
- `[a-zA-Z0-9]{3}` matches three letters or digits, and
- `\.usfm` matches the `.usfm` filename extension.

So, it will match filenames like "57-1Jn.usfm".
